Another obsession of ours...
----------------------------

is the future of awards shows=E2=80=94a cornerstone of the Hollywood
industrial complex that have nonetheless seen declining TV ratings over the=
 past decade. Notably, only 52 percent of respondents said they watch the O=
scars, while a near-majority said they don=E2=80=99t watch any awards shows=
 at all. (Of course, 80 percent of respondents in Entertainment watch the s=
how, but then again, it=E2=80=99s your job!)

As for which movie you think will win best picture this year, we offered an=
other open-ended question, and about 70
percent of you responded. The winner, according to you, will be Wicked, wit=
h Anora and Conclave a distant second and third. I experimented with Google=
=E2=80=99s NotebookLM to help me process all your text inputs, and its take=
 on your responses was that they =E2=80=9Cindicate a notable lack of enthus=
iasm for the Oscars as a whole.=E2=80=9D Ouch! One direct quote from you su=
pporting this synthesis: =E2=80=9CI am in the film and TV business and hone=
stly couldn't care less.=E2=80=9D

Tuning in, dropping out
-----------------------

